In this dir will be (hopefully) carefully explained guides to various
difficult bits about DIL.

If you have any ideas for further installments, and/or criticism with
regard to the current ones, mudmail me.

Gnort

act
---
Explains the use of 'act' in DIL. Also relevant if you are confused about
how to use '$1n' '$2t' etc. in various special routines.

findunit
--------
Explains DIL findunit in detail.

shops
-----
How to make your own shopkeeper.

dil-quest.asc
-------------
A great and very detail DIL example by Icculus. Read it if you  want to
learn DIL.

